# Copy to .secrets/gecko.env at the repository root (see .gitignore).
#
# Live script deps (aiohttp, etc.): use a venv — system Python on Debian/Ubuntu is PEP 668.
#   python3 -m venv .venv-gecko-live && .venv-gecko-live/bin/pip install -r scripts/requirements-live.txt
#   .venv-gecko-live/bin/python3 scripts/verify_shadow_live.py …

# --- Option A: Bearer token (optional) --------------------------------------
# GECKO_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# --- OAuth token cache (optional) -------------------------------------------
# After browser PKCE or password grant, scripts/verify_shadow_live.py writes:
#   .secrets/gecko_oauth.json   (access_token, refresh_token, expires_at)
# Next runs load and refresh automatically unless GECKO_NO_SAVE_TOKEN=1 or --no-save-token.
# GECKO_TOKEN_FILE=/path/to/gecko_oauth.json
# GECKO_NO_SAVE_TOKEN=1

# --- Option B: Browser login (default when no token) ------------------------
# Default: GECKO_OAUTH_REDIRECT=my-home-assistant (or omit)
# Uses https://my.home-assistant.io/redirect/oauth — you do NOT need HA running;
# after login, paste the full browser URL (with ?code= & state=) into the terminal.
# ``/redirect/_change/?redirect=oauth%2F…`` URLs from My Home Assistant are OK too.
#
# If Apple/Auth0 succeeds but the tab never shows my.home-assistant.io: F12 → Network
# → Preserve log → find my.home-assistant.io with code= in the URL and copy Request URL;
# or try Safari / incognito and relax blockers for that tab.
#
# Loopback (127.0.0.1) is NOT allowlisted on Gecko's Auth0 app → "Oops" before login:
# GECKO_OAUTH_REDIRECT=loopback
# GECKO_OAUTH_PORT=8765
#
# Custom HTTPS redirect + paste:
# GECKO_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=https://example.com/callback

# --- Option C: Legacy password grant (often disabled) -----------------------
# GECKO_USERNAME=
# GECKO_PASSWORD=

# GECKO_MONITOR_ID=
# GECKO_ENV_FILE=

# REST API discovery (reuses .secrets/gecko_oauth.json when present; keep dumps under .secrets/)
# Paths come from scripts/gecko_paths_raw_app_1.9.0.txt (Gecko Android 1.9.0 web bundle).
# .venv-gecko-live/bin/python3 scripts/verify_shadow_live.py --dump-api --api-dump-out .secrets/gecko_api_snapshot.json --dump-api-only --api-probe-concurrency 16
# Optional: probe extra templates with stand-in ids (messageId=0, chemicalUse=chlorine, …):
#   … --dump-api-standins --api-dump-out .secrets/gecko_api_snapshot_standins.json
#
# APK mirrors (e.g. APKPure) are not used by this repo. Mapping here is bearer-token GETs only.
# Offline reverse of a vendor APK is a separate, legal/ToS-sensitive research step if you choose it.
